¹³ Species subalterna. Here the word species has changed its meaning. In the original definition it meant a certain relation in which a predicate may stand to its subject. Man is a Species to Socrates. It now means a certain relation in which a subject may stand to its predicate. Man is a Species to Animal. These are generally distinguished by Logicians as the species praedicabilis and the species subjicibilis.
